Sure! Here are some of the best colleges in the USA that provide professional training in horse racing:

1. University of Louisville - Equine Industry Program: The Equine Industry Program at the University of Louisville offers a Bachelor of Science degree in Equine Business. They provide specialized courses in horse racing, including topics like racehorse management, breeding, and sales. [Learn more](https://business.louisville.edu/equine/){:target="_blank"}

2. University of Arizona - Race Track Industry Program: The Race Track Industry Program at the University of Arizona offers a Bachelor of Science degree in Race Track Industry Management. This program focuses on various aspects of the horse racing industry, including racehorse training, track management, and wagering. [Learn more](https://ua-rtip.org/){:target="_blank"}

3. University of Kentucky - Equine Science and Management Program: The Equine Science and Management Program at the University of Kentucky offers a Bachelor of Science degree in Equine Science and Management. This program provides a comprehensive education in all aspects of the equine industry, including horse racing. [Learn more](https://equine.ca.uky.edu/){:target="_blank"}

4. Morrisville State College - Equine Science Program: Morrisville State College offers an Equine Science Program that provides hands-on training in horse racing. Students can choose from various concentrations, including racehorse management and training. [Learn more](https://www.morrisville.edu/program/equine-science){:target="_blank"}

5. SUNY Cobleskill - Equine Studies Program: The Equine Studies Program at SUNY Cobleskill offers a variety of courses related to horse racing, such as racehorse training, equine nutrition, and exercise physiology. They also have an on-campus racetrack for practical training. [Learn more](https://www.cobleskill.edu/academics/school-agriculture-natural-resources/animal-science/equine-studies/){:target="_blank"}

Please note that each college may have specific admission requirements and program details. It is recommended to visit their respective websites for more information.
